reviews.review: Loved all the action and the ending. Are you sure this is the last one? Cause I can easily see a next Star Wars coming along.

My father who is a long time star wars fan said he loved the movie and it made his day. He thinks it was the right move to bring back JJ for this one. He believes JJ has a touch that was missing in the last episode but this was for him, a satisfying conclusion.
I love this franchise so much yet I felt absolutely nothing during this movie. Felt like a desperate attempt for approval from fans. I'm just glad this trilogy is over.

Totally worth seeing. It is a fitting conclusion not only to the new trilogy,  but to the Skywalker saga as a whole. It weaps up Rey's story in a nice little bow, while also serving as a fitting end to Kylo as well.

As a fan I loved it! Some movie critics have expressed that they didn't like the movie because of how JJ made it great for the fans ... well most critics see it once and went to their next assignment. As a fan who will pay to see a few more times in the theater ... i say go see it!!
The movie was good I and all the scenes were exciting to watch.

I really enjoyed it. I'm about 30 years old and have loved Star Wars since before I could remember. I vaguely remember asking my mom to rend empire strikes back when I was about 2 or 3 years old. The story has always inspired me and the universe always intrigues my imagination and the good vs evil elements are always my favorite. I love all the movies however I do understand people's frustration from the Last Jedi, while I enjoy it for what it is and some of the scenes are still very exciting, it was ultimately a filler movie it seems like. Rian Johnson was very selfish in his movie and just wanted to make a movie that was "structured" well but didn't care about what Star Wars meant. The rise of skywalker does its best to save all that while delivering a very exciting and solid ending to the skywalker saga. It is a love letter to Star Wars and very satisfying in many ways even if it is a bit chaotic in the beginning.
Amazing, loved the story, loved the action and loved the fact it made up for the dumpster fire that was The Last Jedi!
The plot was all over the place did not make sense
